cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with image descriptors, which are commonly used in computer vision applications such as object recognition and image retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel means of comparing pixel patches, which involves machine learning techniques, hence it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed descriptor compared to other state-of-the-art descriptors, which involves experimental evaluation, hence it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with image processing techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
